documentation.text:
@dev This is the core functionality of this smart contract.  This function
 reverts if the release time has not been reached yet.  If it has been
 reached, it then checks to ensure that the contract is still in possession
 of the beneficiaries tokens.  If no tokens are available, it reverts.  If
 tokens are available, it then it checks to see if the initialContractBalance
 has been set.  If not set, it will set this value so that it can calculate
 the dispersal rate.
 Next, it uses the current block.timstamp to determine which tranche the
 contract is currently in.  The first evaluation looks to see if the
 contract is fully vested.  If the current tranche is greater than the
 max number of tranches, the contract is fully vested - release all tokens.
 Next, the contract evaluates that the number of tranches released is
 less than the maxTranches value, as well as that the currentTranche is
 greater than the tranchesReleased value.  If both statements evaluate to
 true, this indicates that tokens are available for release.  At this point
 the contract calculates the number of tokens to disperse and transfers them
 to the beneficiary.
 If none of the above conditions apply, this indicates that an early release
 call was made.  In this case, the contract reverts and provides an error.

constructor.details: Constructs the Artemis Time Lock contract.

params._maxTranches: is the total number of tranches that represent the full vesting time for the contract.
params._startTime: is the date/time the vesting schedule starts at.
params._timeLockId: is the numeric ID value that is used to retrieve the address of the corresponding timelock.
params._tranchePercent: is the percentage of tokens that will be released during each tranche period.
params._trancheWeeks: is the number of weeks in each tranche cycle.
params.beneficiary_: is the address where tokens will be distributed to.
params.releaseTime_: is the initial date/time when the release function will be available to call.
params.token_: is the address of the ERC20 token being stored.

release().details: This is the core functionality of this smart contract.  This function reverts if the release time has not been reached yet.  If it has been reached, it then checks to ensure that the contract is still in possession of the beneficiaries tokens.  If no tokens are available, it reverts.  If tokens are available, it then it checks to see if the initialContractBalance has been set.  If not set, it will set this value so that it can calculate the dispersal rate. Next, it uses the current block.timstamp to determine which tranche the contract is currently in.  The first evaluation looks to see if the contract is fully vested.  If the current tranche is greater than the max number of tranches, the contract is fully vested - release all tokens. Next, the contract evaluates that the number of tranches released is less than the maxTranches value, as well as that the currentTranche is greater than the tranchesReleased value.  If both statements evaluate to true, this indicates that tokens are available for release.  At this point the contract calculates the number of tokens to disperse and transfers them to the beneficiary. If none of the above conditions apply, this indicates that an early release call was made.  In this case, the contract reverts and provides an error.

returns._0: the time when the tokens are released.
